#: ../../B/black-hole.rst:5
msgid "black hole"
msgstr "black hole"

#: ../../B/black-hole.rst:7
msgid "n\\.,vt\\."
msgstr "名詞・他動詞"

#: ../../B/black-hole.rst:9
msgid ""
"[common] What data (a piece of email or netnews, or a stream of TCP/IP "
"packets) has fallen into if it disappears mysteriously between its origin "
"and destination sites (that is, without returning a :ref:`bounce-"
"message`\\). \"I think there's a black hole at :code:`foovax`\\!\" conveys "
"suspicion that site :samp:`foovax` has been dropping a lot of stuff on the "
"floor lately (see :ref:`drop-on-the-floor`\\). The implied metaphor of email"
" as interstellar travel is interesting in itself. Readily verbed as "
"blackhole: \"That router is blackholing IDP packets.\" Compare :ref:`bit-"
"bucket` and see :ref:`RBL`\\."
msgstr ""
"[一般的]データ(メールやネットニュースの一片、あるいはTCP/IPパケットの流れ)が、発信元と宛先のサイトの間で(すなわち\\ "
":ref:`bounce-message`\\ を返すこともなく)謎めいて消えたとき、それが落ち込んだ先。「\\ :code:`foovax`\\ "
"にblack holeがあると思う!」は、サイト\\ :samp:`foovax`\\ が最近多くのものを取りこぼしているという疑い(\\ "
":ref:`drop-on-the-floor`\\ "
"を参照)を伝える。メールを恒星間旅行になぞらえる込められた比喩は、それ自体興味深い。blackholeとして容易に動詞化される。「あのルーターはIDPパケットをblackholeしている」。\\"
" :ref:`bit-bucket`\\ と比較せよ。\\ :ref:`RBL`\\ も参照。"
